title: Georges Seurat A Sunday on La Grande Jatte—1884 Poster
description:
Poster developed from Georges Seurat’s A Sunday on La Grande Jatte—1884, 1884/86 from The Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

Inspired by research in optical and color theory, Seurat juxtaposed tiny dots of colors that, through optical blending, form a single and, Seurat believed, more brilliantly luminous hue in the viewer's eye. 

  • Dimensions:  27 x 38 in.
  • Material: Premium Cardstock.
